body:
Hi,
  I understand random gen is NYI (Not Yet Implemented). However, from UVM lib compile/parse perspective it would help to get parser accept srandom() call. Below is a test:

```verilog
package t;

  bit use_uvm_seeding;

  class c;
    function void reseed ();
      if(use_uvm_seeding)
	this.srandom(1);
  endfunction


endclass : c
endpackage

module m;
  import t::*;

  initial begin
  end
endmodule 

```

```log
aa.sv:9: error: Can't find task srandom in class c
aa.sv:9: error: Enable of unknown task ``@.srandom''.
2 error(s) during elaboration.
```

